There's a magical transporter at the bottom of every bottomless pit. <br>
<br>
Cats riding on giant magical stuffed animals are not to be trusted.<br>
<br>
Anyone can become a God, you just have to know the password.<br>
<br>
The purpose of life is to find little keys that let you open the door to where the Cyberdemon is waiting to blow your head off.<br>
<br>
There's always a sequel.<br>
 <p>It IS the thing that goes bump in the night...</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mindslicer>Mindslicer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/ceojoe/wmagsani.gif" BORDER=0> at: 8/23/02 9:37:20 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uascendedbob.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ascended Bob</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/25/02 7:22:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=360.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>    Re: 10 things you've learned from games.</span><hr size=1> RPG<br>
Enemies randomly appear out of thin air.<br>
<br>
If you are walking in a rather narrow hallway and an enemy appears out of thin air the hallway expands to a size large enough to accomodate not only a rather huge enemy but three or four of them. <br>
<br>
You will then proceed to fight. First you hit them as hard as you can and then you stand still and allow them to do the same.<br>
<br>
There is no such thing as geological diversity. Plants, people, art, machinery and what have you will look the same all over the planet. In certain forest there will be differences from the surrounding area, however, there is a ten to one chance there is a forest like that everywhere else in the world.<br>
<br>
When travelling from town to town you will grow around 100 times larger and go many miles in just a few steps. When you are this big you can't climb mountains though or walk in the ocean.<br>
<br>
FPS<br>
You cannot turn your head. You may have eyes on either side though.<br>
<br>
There is no one else but you to fight an entire planet/city/spacestation full of bad guys. However during your escape or travelling somewhere else, its possible for you to operate a vehicle, requring a crew of highly trained specialists, all by yourself.<br>
<br>
When falling from a high place you will not die. However if you live somwhere in which that does not hold true, when you fall from a high place you will remain upright while still holding your gun.<br>
<br>
When you get hurt your eyes flash red. <br>
<br>
Driving<br>
You can master inertial drift, purchase racing slicks, upgrade your exhaust, tune your shocks and spoilers, trick out your drivetrain, and survive a 200+ mph crash into a wall with no car damage or injuries.<br>
<br>
You also cannot turn your head, but may have eyes on the back of your head.<br>
<br>
You can climb a mountain that is damn near vertical. You can then fall from 100 foot cliffs and survive. Your truck may or may not lose a headlight.<br>
<br>
Your car does not have a steering wheel. If it does you don't have hands.<br>
<br>
Stealing a car is verrrrrry easy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mindslicer>Mindslicer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/ceojoe/wmagsani.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/25/02 4:54:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=360.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/ceojoe/mindslicer.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:  Re: 10 things you've learned from games.</span><hr size=1> Even though you have no legs (as I mentioned above) you can pick of items with your invisible feet.<br>
